2. Definitions

"Affiliate" means any person or entity that directly or indirectly Controls,
is Controlled by, or is under common Control with another person or entity.

"Control" means the direct or indirect power to direct management, policies,
or material business decisions, whether through ownership of voting interests,
by contract, or otherwise. "Common Control" means Control by the same person,
entity, or coordinated group of persons or entities.

"Competing Offering" means any product, service, or feature made available to
a third party on a hosted, managed, software-as-a-service, application
programming interface, platform-as-a-service, embedded, OEM, or similar basis
that uses, incorporates, embeds, is derived from, or provides access to the
Licensed Work or a material portion of its functionality, and that
substitutes for, competes with, or is marketed as a substitute for the
Licensed Work or for any product or service the Licensor offers using the
Licensed Work.

"Gross Revenue" means total revenue from all sources, measured for you and
your Affiliates on a consolidated basis using the accounting principles
ordinarily applied in the normal course of business, applied consistently and
without excluding Affiliates or shifting revenue among commonly controlled
persons or entities to reduce the amount counted under this License.

"Non-Production Use" means use solely for evaluation, development,
integration, testing, continuous integration, quality assurance, staging,
demonstrations, training, education, benchmarking, or security review or
research, whether performed internally or for a specific customer, and not
for running ordinary production workloads or providing a live production
service to third parties.

"Personnel" means natural persons performing services for you or any
Affiliate, including employees and individual contractors, whether full-time,
part-time, temporary, seasonal, or engaged through an agency or similar
intermediary. Personnel is measured for you and your Affiliates on a
consolidated basis as the average monthly number of such persons during the
relevant fiscal year.

"Production Use" means any use of the Licensed Work other than Non-Production
Use, including use in a live environment for internal operations or to provide
products or services to third parties.

"Version" means each separately identified release, tag, or other public
distribution of the Licensed Work first made available by Licensor. If
Licensor makes public a snapshot of the Licensed Work without a release label,
that public snapshot is its own Version.

