4. Permitted Use and Production Limits

You may use the Licensed Work for Non-Production Use.

You may use the Licensed Work for Production Use only if, at the time of that
Production Use and measured across you and your Affiliates on a consolidated
basis for the most recently completed fiscal year, all of the following are
true:

1. the Production Use is not part of a Competing Offering;
2. Gross Revenue did not exceed US$10,000,000; and
3. Personnel was fewer than 100.

If there is no completed fiscal year yet for you or your Affiliates, apply
the same test using a good-faith estimate for the current fiscal year on a
consolidated basis.

You may not avoid these limits by splitting activities, revenue, workforce,
or ownership across multiple entities, holding companies, contractors, or
other arrangements under common Control. The consolidated measurement rules in
this License control.

If any one of the conditions above is not satisfied, you may not engage in
Production Use under this License. A separate commercial license from
Licensor is required before any such Production Use.

